<br>
Vulak is pretty much not part of the agreement, near as I can tell, because a force that is just doing NToV for the first, second, third time or so barely stands a chance.<br>
<br>
When we've had NToV, guilds that wanted to do Vulak asked us if it was OK, so that may drop some doubt on whether or not Vulak is actually part of the agreement, but I'm inclined to say that it's because there are dragons 'in the way' on the way to the Vulak ring that would be part of the agreement that the guild currently in NToV hasn't done yet.<br>
<br>
Back a while ago, round about the time GC was in NToV, there was at least a gentleman's rule that if the server rebooted/etc and you had killed Aary the previous day, you got the first shot at him. Whether that was by circumstance or consideration, I'm unsure as I was only a tag-along with GC on occassion at that point. Now, at least, at least one guild NToV capable doesn't think that's the case (which is fine by me, provided they don't send members of the guild who killed Aary the prior day telling them to 'stay the F*** out of NToV, it's ours' ... -- guild name withheld because this isn't the rant forum!). <br>
<br>
There have been cases where guilds capable of NToV ceding remaining dragons to another guild, though in our case at least, the twice that this has happend the 3-day window had already passed. There was still communication between our guild and the guild who had killed Aary, and had they said 'no' we wouldn't have gone after the stragglers.<br>
<br>
As far as guilds doing NToV regularly, I can only speak of those whom I've seen in NToV. I don't know that there is the rat race for it there used to be, so no guilds are actively tapping their foot 4 hours before Aary's spawn time, due to the fact that most of the equipment available in NToV (for us at least) is minor upgrades at this point, not the Monty Haul it used to be for guilds. The guilds I've seen recently:<br>
<br>
Sans Requiem (obviously =)<br>
Divine Prophecy (who got aary again last night)<br>
Dominion<br>
Quiet Solitude (mostly done but *are* attempting Vulak Ring?)<br>
Hawkestone<br>
<br>
And I've seen Force of One call the camp, they got Aary once with Genaden tanking for them (or so says their web page) but last time they were calling the camp, Aary was still up when they left. Not saying this to start a flame or anything, but I'm not sure that qualifies as 'In NToV regularly' when held to the letter.<br>
<br>
There may be others, but they're not in timezones when I'm around.<br>
